** Editor's note: Located in the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau in southwestern China, it is known as the "roof of the world". It is the most developed area of the world's glaciers and the source of many important rivers in Asia. It is also a key area and sensitive area for global climate change. In April this year, China passed the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau Ecological Protection Law and will be officially implemented on September 1. Among them, the study of "strengthening climate change, biodiversity, ecological protection and restoration, hydrological water resources, snow mountain and glaciers in the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau". Studies must first enter the field. Geological scholar Yang Yong has been investigated and studied the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau since the 1980s. In June this year, he was inspected on the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau. He sent us inspection notes last year and this year for many consecutive months, and used first -hand information to show the most primitive records in the wild work and the status of the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau under climate change. **

In May this year, I entered the southeast of Tibet along Hengdou Mountain. Now crossing the lake group on the middle of the north of Tibet, entering the Taklama Gaman Desert in Xinjiang from the Ali Line 219.

In the past three decades, I went to the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau for inspection almost every year. I have experienced the impact of climate change in myself. I also witnessed the changes in the environment and ecology of this "third pole of the earth" and the "Asian Water Tower". In the past few years, El Niopy is likely to happen, or leads to extreme heating up, which has brought many challenges to the climate, hydrology and ecological environment of the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau, which makes me very worried.

The last time the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau Inspection was 2022. My friend, Mr. Ren Wenjie (Chairman of Ningbo Fei Shi), set off from "Bing Chasha" in April -that is, Bingzhong Luo, Yunnan, in observing Walong Township, and reached the Tibet Line in Chada, Tibet -entered Tibet. In this development area of marine glaciers, I watched the Sabapa glaciers, the Qiaqing Glacier, the Czepu Glacier, and the Rinlonbaka Glacier. In July, we first followed the Himalayas, from Yang Zhuoyong to the Shiquan River in Ali, and inspected the river lake along the way. After returning to Lhasa, he turned to the north to Yuedoura Mountain, passed through the Sanjiang source, then turned over Kunlun Mountain, west along the northern slope of Kunlun Mountain, and reached the Alki Mountains into the West Chaidama Basin. Back to Sichuan in early August. This half was inspected in Gobi, seasonal rivers, Yadan and Salt Lake. Two new Yadan development areas were also found during the inspection.

![](Images/FT Chinese Free Version/2023-07-09T23-42-39-00-00/000186995_piclink.jpg)The coloring of the Laotang Plateau in northern Tibet. The source of the water mainly comes from the glacial melting of the glacier in the south slope of the Tanggula Mountains. Due to the accelerated melting of the Glacier of the Tang Gula Mountain in the climate, the lake has continued to expand in recent years, and the water area is approaching Nami and Qinghai Lake. Picture source: Yang Yong

The inspection is to see the marine glaciers and the Asian continental glaciers in Tibet. Choose April and July because April was the time when the avalanche was high in the southeast of Tibetan, and July was the main flood season. Observing the environment of the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau in different hydrological season can get a more comprehensive understanding. Moreover, in 2022, high temperature and drought, maybe you will see a special hydrological scene.

**high temperature**

It is hard to imagine that the biggest feeling for me to go to the glacier is "hot". During the process of crossing the north this year, it was originally a precipitation season, but every day it was like a sun, and the earth was yellowish.

During the July inspection last year, I didn't seem to be in high altitudes, but in the summer of the Mainland. I remember that in the 1980s, in this season, I needed to wear coats and even cold clothes during the day. In recent years, the sun has been exposed to the sun during the day, and wearing short -sleeved shorts is enough. If it rains or winds, the temperature will decrease, and it will feel cold until night.

Many wetlands, grasslands, or desertized sandy areas around many glaciers have a maximum temperature of more than 30 degrees or even more than 40 degrees.

This is the norm in the plateau. In mid -August in the past few years, we measured the highest temperature of 46 degrees in the ground environment of Zeng Songquan desert in the southwest of the West Snow Mountain West Slot of the Ladan Winter Winter Snow Mountain. In January 2021, I was in Grade Gula, the source of the Yangtze River, and I hadn't set up a heavy snow. Our snow -proof equipment has not been used. The hot sun during the day is roasted, and the surface of the glacier is engraved with deep flowing water.

On the surface of the glacier, we measured more than 10 degrees, and the ice body was above zero, which shocked me a little. Glacier is like an environment similar to oven. It looks very fragile, as if it will quickly melt and collapse quickly.

**glacier**

I have visited the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau many times in the past 30 years and recorded multiple glaciers. Marine glaciers are frequent in snow, and flood disasters often occur. A large amount of stone, soil, and ice crickets are left on the surface of the glacier and next to the glacier. We all observe the traces of retreating through these.

From the beginning of the 1980s to the present, the retreat of several glaciers in the Yangtze River source area is very obvious. For example, according to the contrast between field measurement and satellite images, Gangjiaquba Glacier has retreated more than 2,000 meters in the past half century, while Jiang Gudi Ru Ru Northern Glacier has retreated more than 500 meters.

Jeima Yangzong Glacier in the western section of the Himalayas is the source of the Yarlung Zangbo River. I saw that the ice -cut ice wall at the front of the glacier had become a broken ice slope, and a large ice lake was formed at the front end. It was about 400 meters after 12 years.

![](Images/FT Chinese Free Version/2023-07-09T23-42-39-00-00/000186996_piclink.jpg)Tibetan marine glacier. Picture source: Yang Yong

During the investigation, I can even hear the sound of water flow and stones from the glacier. In the first stage of the icing tongue, the residual ice tower and the lone ice peaks separated from glaciers are basically unavailable now, indicating that the melting speed of glaciers in recent years is very fast. The front of the glacier is widened, and the ice crickets are flattened, and they are rarely accumulated into a mound. More than 20 kilometers of the source flow section of Qinqu on the upper reaches of the Langhe River, the tributary of the valley glaciers on both sides, and the cross -strait of the Chezu Mito River bed, you can see dozens of large glacier mudslides and ice stones full of riverbeds. In Rinlongbaka Glacier and Anima Qing Glacier, we also encountered glaciers' floods.

China has carried out two glaciers, that is, register the location, height, area and volume of the glacier one by one, and arranged it into a book. Data show that from the mid -to -late 1950s to around 2014, China's glacier area was reduced by 18%. Among them, the Glacier area of the Glacier area of the Himalayas and Himalayas in the south of the Ganglazi Shandong section in the south of the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau and the Shanxi section of the Himalayan section has the fastest atrophy, and the average annual atrophy is as high as 2.2%per year.

The retreat of glacier is only a phenomenon that can be observed on the surface. In fact, tens of thousands of ice lakes are distributed in the Himalayas. The melting and retreat of glaciers have expanded the ice lake, causing serious losses in the underwater ice. Studies have shown that from 2000 to 2020, about 2.7 billion tons of underwater ice quality losses were underestimated.

**water**

July and August are the main flood season, and it should be the most abundant time. However, it was rare in these two inspections. Compared with the normal years of previous years, the water flow of the river is very small. The beaches of some rivers are exposed, and most of the reservoirs are in low water level.

![](Images/FT Chinese Free Version/2023-07-09T23-42-39-00-00/000186997_piclink.jpg)In recent years, the continuous drought of the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau has decreased in precipitation after summer. Many rivers have decreased flow. Reservoir and power stations are generally at low water levels. Picture source: Yang Yong

In addition to the glacier melting to bring a lot of replenishment to the river lake, there is also the water supplement brought by the thawing of frozen soil. Studies have shown that compared with the beginning of this century, the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau has many years of frozen soil area to the middle of the 21st century (2030 to 2050), which will decrease by about 39%, and by the end of the 21st century (2080 to 2100), it will decrease by 81%. It is difficult to imagine what is the scene of a Qinghai -Tibet Plateau that is basically not frozen.

The increase in the number of lakes and the expansion of the area is not necessarily a good thing. As for my personal observation, it is more about the evolution and unpredictable disasters of the river water system. During the previous inspection, I saw the Big Gongbut Mountains collapsed and landslide in 2000 to form a large flood in the lower reaches of the Yarlung Tibetan River. In 2012, the rising decision of the Coco Xili table formed a new riverbed, and the pattern of the flowing water system inside and outside the north of the Yangtze River was changing.

A achievement of the scientific investigation of the second Qinghai-Tibet Plateau in China in 2017 shows that from 1980 to 2018, the solid water of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau accelerated melting, and liquid water increased. Mainly the increase in liquid water in the internal flow area in the north, and the liquid water in some watershed in the southern outflow area shows a reduction trend. Scientists use "imbalances" to describe the impact of the "Asian Water Tower" under climate change, and believe that the contradiction between supply and demand of water may become increasingly serious.

Moreover, the water of the river lake seems to increase, but it destroys the water cycle, which may lead to a decrease in water volume. A study of land water resources in the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau published in 2022 found that the land water reserves of the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau from 2002 to 2017 decreased at a rate of about 10 billion m³/year. Seriously threatened its water supply capacity.

** Grassland degradation and desertification **

In the hot Baojie Basin more than 10 kilometers away from the Jaya Yangzong glacier, we saw the ending of the glacier when the glacier was advancing during the small ice period, that is, when the glaciers were temporarily stable, the monopoly position formed on the front end of the accumulation of the front end was formed. terrain. The flood seductive covers dozens of square kilometers in the basin. Today the basin is more like a drought and silent desert.

In the past, the Qiangtang Plateau and Coco, at first glance, were green and sparse green, showing a large amount of vegetation coverage. In recent years, many places here look more like desert or gray Gobi. In the Yangtze River source area and even the upper reaches of the Tongtian River, the upper reaches of the Yellow River, the upper reaches of the Yarlung Zangbo River, and the hinterland of the cocoa, the dunes are getting taller and taller, and they have spread to the desert.

In the past 20 years, the scope of human activities in the Tang Dynasty Plateau and the Sanjiangyuan area has become wider and wider, and the grazing has exceeded 5,500 meters above sea level. The range of grazing has penetrated into the "restricted areas" of cocoa Coco and northern Tibet. Many of the original nomadic areas can be grazing all year round, and even settled in the administrative village under the glacier of the Yangtze River. More than 20 years ago, more than 20 years ago, the "unmanned area" has now been "permanent" for human beings.

![](Images/FT Chinese Free Version/2023-07-09T23-42-39-00-00/000186998_piclink.jpg)Northern Tibetan Nami Wo Wo Lake shore herdsmen's pasture. Picture source: Yang Yong

In the Yangtze River source area, the closest to Jiang Guding's sand dune chain is only about 20 kilometers. Under the Que Moshan, we found several new -monthly crescent dunes. I don't remember these sand dunes when I passed here in the 1980s.

**Influence**

As for what I have experienced and seeing, the impact of climate change on the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau is mainly manifested in the rise of temperature, rising snow lines, retreat of glaciers, evolution of water systems, grassland degradation, desertification expansion, etc. A series of composite disaster chains have the greatest impact on humans, and at the same time, the natural ecosystem is also facing unknown risks.

In recent years, in the predible Tibetan area, the mountain collapse has formed a large dammed lake, which then collapses and causes the flood to form a disaster chain. There are also many dammed lakes in the southern slope of the Himalayas to make floods. In 2019, the upper reaches of the Jinsha River, the Grand Canyon of the Yarlung Tibetan River, has occurred similar to geological disasters.

Although it continued to high temperature and drought in 2022, there were also heavy rain and snowfall in local areas. Extreme disaster weather is common.

![](Images/FT Chinese Free Version/2023-07-09T23-42-39-00-00/000186999_piclink.jpg)The dry hot river valley of the Jinsha River has intensified degradation in the process of climate change. Picture source: Yang Yong

The Zhuo Nai Lake of Coco was originally a inland saltwater lake. After the rise of the water surface, it collapsed, shaping a new river, which is connected with the Yangtze River water system, and from an inner flow system to the outer water system. Zhuo Nai Lake may also evolve into a freshwater lake. Each year, Tibetan antelopes will gather to the Lady Lake. Whether its change will affect the habitat environment and the function of the Tibetan antelope and the function of the "big delivery room".

My intuitive feeling can also be confirmed with scientific research to see the impact of climate change on the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau.

In 2019, a research results of the Chinese Academy of Sciences on the global water tower showed that the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau is one of the most intense regions of the world's warming. The new disaster includes glaciers accelerated, lake surface expansion, glacier runoff, and frequent ice collapse. Among the 78 water tower units around the world, the Asian Water Tower occupies 16 units, and it is also the most important, vulnerable and most risky.

In April 2022, the "Third Polar Environmental Science Evaluation Report" issued by the UN Environment Agency believes that the intensification of water circulation has caused geological disasters such as ice lakes and Bingnan. The Qinghai -Tibet Plateau will further become warm and humid at the end of this century, which may cause more geological disasters.

The threat of climate change to the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau is multi -faceted and long -term. Perhaps at the inflection point, we need to take a serious understanding and response. Now, I am on the way to investigate the Qinghai -Tibet Plateau, not only to record but also to protect.

** Author's profile: Yang Yong, president of Hengduan Mountain Research Association, chief scientist. He was one of the earliest people who went deep into the upper reaches of the Yangtze River and the Yarlung Zangbo River to investigate the geology and hydrological environment of the river. **

