Because the firearms were strictly controlled, there was almost no shooting in China, but it was not uncommon to attack with a knife. Many knife -holding injuries are the goal of schools. In August last year, an attacker in a kindergarten in Jiangxi Province, China [Killing](https://www.cbsnews.com/news/china-kindergarten-stabbing-3-killed-6-wounded/)Three people, causing six people to be injured. In 2021, the attack in a kindergarten in Guangxi, Southwest China caused [died of two people](https://abcnews.go.com/International/18-injured-stabbing-kindergarten-southern-china/story?id=77368307)16 were injured.

advertise

Especially in [a series of series in 2010](https://www.nytimes.com/2010/05/13/world/asia/13china.html)After more than 20 people's death (including 19 children) school attacks, the government called on the school to strengthen security. The attackers of such cases are usually repeated, and some of them are sentenced to death.

Authorities often blame these people with "resentment" or want to "revenge society](https://cn.nytimes.com/china/20191113/china-chemical-attack/)". Experts and [some officials](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8681873.stm)It has been said that these attackers are dissatisfied with the rapid changes in China and social pressures such as unemployment. However, China's psychological health and medical resources are still scarce, and the social security network is also weak.

The government also strictly controls the spread of such attacks and other tragedy related information. The names of the victims are usually not disclosed, and their relatives sometimes be stunned.

