During the visit, Brinken told reporters that the two countries had agreed to "build a working group or collaborative plan" to crack down on Fentney smuggling. But just a few days later, the US federal prosecutor [announced the prosecution](https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/23/nyregion/china-fentanyl-companies-charged.html)Four Chinese companies accused them of illegal trafficking chemicals, and made a large number of Fentany sold to the United States through the Mexican drug trafficking group, and the cooperation prospects of the two countries became dim.

