Recently, the US Federal Supreme Court, which has already completed conservatives, made a judgment, withdrawing the "correction" admitted by Harvard University and North Carolina State University to the new students.(affirmative action)Essence This problem was originally one of the "gunpowder barrels" that the United States had been arguing for a long time, and the popularity of judging in the United States can be imagined. It is also a "sensitive issue" that Asians, especially Chinese, are concerned, because they generally believe that the rectification of college enrollment is not good for Asians and white people. Starting at least in the 2020 presidential election, the US issue has always been the focus of Chinese people at home and abroad. Together with the previous abortion judgments, homosexual wedding cakes, and webpage customized judgments made by the Supreme Court, these issues have generated fierce and lasting controversy in the WeChat group. The argument itself is a good thing, and it is not so good to become mutual.

At the invitation of a group of friends, I also commented on the judgment in a WeChat group. I did not expect to be involved in the vortex of controversy at once. Because my "US Federal Constitution" and other books cannot be updated in China, I do not have enough time and motivation to track the US constitutional jurisprudence in recent years, so my so -called "comment" is actually the analysis ideas and ideas in this field. Background introduction. I have made a "prevention needle" in advance. I did not closely track the progress of the United States university correction in nearly ten years. I don't know much about today's specific situation. However, I have studied the constitutional process of the United States for more than 200 years. Nature, analysis methods and the real dilemma they are facing. Therefore, I did not observe the specific conclusion of supporting the judgment, but only adopted the "golden mean" position: both sides were a bit reasonable. The problem of this boss was time to reflect and adjust.

Unexpectedly, this position has attracted the criticism of many left -wing people, accusing me of not being criticized by criticizing the Supreme Court with the "mainstream" intellectual industry in the United States. Some of them are for specific issues, such as the exception of the military school? But there are also some on the outline, even suspected of attacking abuse. I support me and I started to talk to each other in the group, and my words were very polite. I also leave a message again to clarify that the qualitative criticism as "extreme left" may also make some opponents unhappy. I was worried that this debate was the same as before, and finally dispersed; the problem was not clearly discussed, and the attack on each other worsened each other's feelings.

Since the Liberty and the new left "big division" in the 1990s, the US elections have split the "liberal" (more "progressive") and "conservatives" that were originally inside the liberals. If the Russian and Ukraine War may have a split in the conservatives, the disputes this time mainly occur in the Liberal camp against Trump. Regardless of left and right, freedom or conservative, this phenomenon is common in the WeChat group of Jianzhong. As long as there are different opinions, they will have a mutual conversation and finally dispersal. To sum up in a word from the great leader, politics originally had to make a lot of themselves, and the enemy did it. Today, China ’s liberals do the opposite, and keep making themselves less.

** 2. Freedom and tolerance **

On the surface, this seems very natural. The so -called "liberal" is to be a jealous temperament, not only has independent opinions, but also expresses the chest and casual expression. If you have to obey "organizational discipline" and forced "pace consistent", it is not a liberal. However, this is just one aspect of "freedom". If freedom refers to his own pleasure, then the dictator will become the most "free" person in the world.

Of course, the "freedom" of liberalism not only refers to its own freedom, but also refers to respecting the freedom of others -not only simply let people speak (you do not have power, you can't let people speak), but in your heart and and Different opinions on attitude. "Tolerance" is not "harder", not to talk about right and wrong, but just not treating himself as God, thinking that he has mastered the absolute truth, the other party is either stupid or evil. Almost any issue, there will be different opinions between people. If you think that others are wrong, of course, you can criticize directly, but in most cases, these questions do not have a simple correct answer. If you think your answer is absolutely correct, it is likely to be simple because you want to be simple.

Mortal is wise, and human wisdom is limited. Human morality and judgment ability is roughly equal, and those who disagree with me may be right -not acknowledging this, it can only show that you are not liberals, but a dictator who only respects. Since everyone makes mistakes, you are roughly the same as others. Why are you absolutely correct confidence? Therefore, when there are different opinions, I will first reflect on myself to see if there is a reason for the opposition; if there is a reason, it will be corrected. But even in this case, I have to retain the minimum respect for the other party. Maybe my reflection has not played a role. It proves that he was right afterwards?

Therefore, tolerance is not a "humility" that is high above, but the honesty of a basic fact -we are all people, not God; we have a cognitive ability, but everyone's cognition has obvious limitations. We can hardly say to others seriously, "You are wrong!" - Who do you yourself? Why must others be wrong, not yourself? Putting yourself in the position of God, just as ridiculous as his guest appearances at other people's homes. Anyone who knows it should not do this. With a tolerance mentality, there will be no more abusive attacks, aggressive, and ridicule in the WeChat group.

It can be seen that the reason why these phenomena happened so that the liberals made themselves less and less, the root cause is that we are not really a real liberal. On the contrary, we are self -righteous dictators who like to overlook our opinions on others. After a few rounds, of course, all of them have become "lonely people." If you can't tolerate different opinions sincerely, you can't be a true liberal. Hu Shi said, "Tolerance is more important than freedom", this should be one of the meanings. True liberals tolerate others from the heart will always retain space for different opinions, and tolerance is the adhesive of a free community. Since they are tolerant of each other and treat each other, at least they don't quarrel, why do they still make them less? Based on the tolerance, the power of the free community will continue to grow and grow.

Of course, tolerance is not a bottomless line. If you make mistakes on the so -called "big right" issue, you cannot be "tolerant". If a person violates the basic rights such as political natural law, disrespect the freedom of belief, freedom of speech, negative equality (anti -discrimination), etc., or does not accept basic systems such as democracy, administrative neutrality, and judicial independence, then you can determine that this person and liberals can be determined no common language. Since countless historical facts have proven that such views have endlessly harmed, the "tolerance" of such views has become a principle of indulgence. But under the premise of respecting the political natural law, all different opinions are part of the free community and should be tolerant of each other.

** Three, distinguish the principles and details **Although the political natural law is the standard for judging the right and wrong, not all issues involve such principles, at least most of the problems are not as simple as 1+1 = 2. Negative equality (not discrimination) is an absolute laws of political nature, but positive and equal measures such as correction action are not. This difference is just as simple as "I can't hurt you", which is not the same as "I must do good deeds for you". Of course, negative and positive are not always so clear; historical discrimination may cause long -term harm to the victims, so that it requires certain positive measures to achieve negative equality. This is the original intention of President Kennedy's proposal to "rectify the action". Needless to repeat it, but this does not eliminate the essence of the two. After 60 years of implementation, its social controversy is getting bigger and bigger. A sampling survey shows that most Americans do not agree with the rectification of college admissions. Although most scholars seem to support the big goal of correction action, criticism of specific means such as college enrollment ethnic quotas is still endless. Almost at the beginning, the rectification of college enrollment was accused as the main benefit of the middle and upper and upper -level African applicants, which was mainly a good -looking, and could not help the lower -level black families who were trapped in poverty, drug abuse, and domestic violence. In other words, correction really allows more black students in the university campus, but contributed very much to solving the increasing black problem in American society. In this way, the focus of policies may not be the actions of university enrollment and correction, but to allow students of different ethnic groups to enjoy primary and secondary school education with basic equality and curb the increasingly bad trend of basic education quality and environmental gaps in different regions. Perhaps the economic conditions of the family are more related factors than the ethnic group -why do black people of a wealthy family have more competitive advantages than white people in a poor family? Perhaps family income is a more related factors than ethnic groups. Taking care of poor students can help the bottom black people and realize the diversification of real ethnic groups. In this sense, the simple ethnic quota system definitely constitutes "reverse discrimination".

In fact, the judgment of the Supreme Court did not overthrow any precedent in this field. It has neither denying the importance of the diversification of the university campus nor the constitutionality of considering the ethnic group as the admission factor, but just denies the specific enrollment plan of the two schools of Harvard and North Carolina. As Harvard University responds to this judgment, American universities can still take campus diversification as the goal and consider ethnic factors during enrollment. However, the enrollment scheme requires more stringent constitutional standards for ethnic diversification. Even if the leftists agree, the ethnic quota system is too simple and arbitrarily. For example, the enrollment plan in the "Michigan University Admission Case" in 2003 locks the proportion of black admission to the proportion of black applicants. This is obviously unreasonable. Therefore, the US academic community's response to this verdict is not a negative denial, but mainly because of more concerns that stricter judicial standards may make the campus diversification more difficult to achieve. If the ethnic quota is not desirable, what kind of enrollment solution can truly achieve diversified goals? Since this question does not have a standard answer, why not discuss specific issues calmly and and have to determine a self -conscious position and verbal with different opinions?

The correction action is not absolutely correct, the more the better, because the number of college admission places is limited after all, and too many African or Western descent will inevitably squeeze the places of other ethnic groups such as white people and Asians. Similarly, there is no simple standard answer in the abortion of the Supreme Court and the equal right to belief, because they involve conflicts between different rights. If you go to extremes and protect one party's rights too much, it will inevitably harm the rights of the other party. As long as you do n’t take the extreme, there are more rights and less rights.

