Comprehensive Reuters and Frenchwang reported that Turkish President's Office issued a statement on Sunday (July 9) stating that Erdogan and Biden held a telephone talk. Erdogan told Biden on the phone that in order to get Turkey's approval to join NATO, Sweden took action in the right direction, but these actions did not have any effect, because although Sweden passed the counter -terrorism legislation, the Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) Supporters are still demonstrating in Sweden.

Sweden's application for joining NATO has not yet received support from Turkey and Hungary, a member of NATO.

