The NATO Summit is about to be held, and Sweden hopes to get qualifications for NATO member states during the summit.

Erdogan and Biden also agreed to hold a face -to -face meeting at the NATO Summit to exchange opinions on bilateral relations and regional issues.

The two also mentioned the matters of the F-16 fighter to the United States, and the Turkish President's Office said in a statement that Turkey's efforts to get the F-16 fighter with Sweden to join NATO are "incorrect."

In addition, Erdogan and Biden also discussed the issue of Ukraine's expectations to join NATO in the call.

