More than 2 million people in Fukuoka Prefecture, Hiroshima Prefecture, Saga County, Yamaguchi County and Daxian County received a lower -level warning to persuade them to evacuate in dangerous areas.

The Japanese government has a level 5 evacuation order, but cannot force people to leave their homes.

