Satoshisugimoto, director of the Meteorological Forecasting Department of the Japan Meteorological Agency, told reporters: "The city governments of Fukuoka Prefecture have issued special alerts for heavy rain. This is the most severe rainfall in the history of the (region) ... It is necessary to ensure personal safety if it causes life to danger. "

