![](Images/cnnytimes/2023-07-10T10-46-21-08-00/09dc-USCHINA-cjhq-master1050.jpg)Minister of Finance [Jennite Yellen](https://cn.nytimes.com/usa/20230706/janet-yellen-china-treasury/)Visit China with the hope of restarting relations with China. The US -China relations, which have been deteriorating in recent years, have recently lost control. The reason is that the two sides are opposed to several major issues, including the Ukrainian war and China, which leads the U.S. -U.S. airspace [spy balloon](https://cn.nytimes.com/usa/20230206/china-spy-balloon-time/)Shooted down by the U.S. military, and the two countries' mutual [restricting trade](https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/08/business/economy/us-china-chips-janet-yellen.html)The practice is constantly upgrading.

After ten hours of talks in Beijing in Beijing, Yellen said at a press conference on Sunday that she believed that the United States and China had a more stable foothold, although there were "major differences" in the two countries.

"We believe that the world is big enough to accommodate the prosperity and development of our two countries," Yellen said.

Yellen announced that the two sides will communicate more frequently at the highest level. She refers to the relationship between the two countries as "one of the most important relationships in our era" and say that improving the dialogue is to prevent deepening of reluctance and prevent this relationship. Way. A few weeks ago, Secretary of State [Brinken](https://cn.nytimes.com/china/20230619/blinken-china-xi-diplomacy/)Visit China. Later this month, a special envoy of the presidential climate change affairs [John Kerry](https://cn.nytimes.com/usa/20230707/john-kerry-china-climate/)It will also visit China to restart the negotiation of global warming.

advertise

However, economic tensions are unlikely to be substantially relieved. Yellen has returned to Washington on Sunday without announced that it has made breakthrough progress or reached an agreement to make up for the continuous cracks between the two countries. Yellen clearly stated that the Biden government has expressed serious concerns about many business behaviors in China, including China's approach to foreign companies and the policy of being regarded by the United States as economic coercion.

Yellen's trip was the first time in the past four years to visit China. She saw the four most powerful leaders in the leadership of Xi Jinping in the leadership team of Xi Jinping: Premier Li Qiang, Chinese official No. 2, and Yellen The position is equivalent [Deputy Prime Minister He Lifeng](https://cn.nytimes.com/china/20230328/xi-jinping-he-lifeng-china-economy/), Minister of Finance Liu Kun, and Pan Gongsheng, the new party secretary of the People's Bank of China.

![](Images/cnnytimes/2023-07-10T10-46-21-08-00/09dc-USCHINA-jqkl-master1050.jpg)Last Saturday, Yellen (left) met with the Vice Premier He Lifeng (right) in Beijing in Beijing. This is part of her 10 -hour talks in the past two days. POOL Photo by Markschiefelbein

A few hours before Yellen held a press conference, the Chinese official news agency Xinhua News Agency issued a report on her interview, saying that the talks between the two parties were constructive, but also reiterated the key areas that China believed to be controversial. It is reported that China continues to oppose the Bayeng government emphasizing that it is to maintain US national security through trade restrictions.

"China believes that generalization of national security is not conducive to normal economic and trade exchanges," Xinhua News Agency reported. "China has expressed concerns about the US sanctions restrictions on China."

US -China relations have a significant impact on the world. The two countries are the largest and second largest economies in the world, accounting for 40%of the global output, and they are still indispensable partners in many aspects. The two countries buy and sell important products, provide funds for each other's business and business, and make applications and movies for audiences in the two countries.

Chinese officials expressed their concerns to Yellen. Yellen said that they discussed the Trump administration's tariff on tariffs on imported goods in China, and these tariffs were still retained. Although Yellen had criticized tariffs invalid, she said that before the end of the internal review, the current government will not make any decisions on tariffs, which has reiterated the government position after President Biden took office.

advertise

She also mentioned that China is about to invest in the United States [restricting investment in China](https://www.nytimes.com/2023/02/09/business/us-china-investing-tech-biden.html)Farewell, and said that she tried to explain that these measures were aimed at certain limited industries, not to have a broad impact on the Chinese economy. Chinese officials and experts are also worried that the US government's efforts to restrict China's efforts may damage the development of high potential industries such as artificial intelligence and quantum computing in China.

China has been restricting its country's overseas investment since 2015, encouraging Chinese enterprises and individuals to avoid overseas real estate speculation, and promote them [to make larger investment in areas with strategic value](https://cn.nytimes.com/business/20190311/china-central-bank-currency/)For example, aircraft production, heavy equipment manufacturing, and network security.

![](Images/cnnytimes/2023-07-10T10-46-21-08-00/09dc-USCHINA-qzlt-master1050.jpg)Marine container in the port of Los Angeles, St. Pedro, California. Yellen said that the Trump administration's tariffs on imported goods in China will remain unchanged. Coley Brown for the Newyork Times

Wu Xinbo, dean of the School of International Relations of Shanghai Fudan University, warned that Yellen's trip will not bring substantial improvements in relations between the two countries unless the Bayeng government changes its policy of China.

"So far, we have not seen any signs that Biden will re -consider his economic policy to China," Wu Xinbo said.

Some analysts believe that the desire to make more dialogues is a major progress. After several months of ignoring each other, the two countries can at least start discussing differences.

Former Chinese Ministry of Commerce officials and now Beijing's global think tank as a senior researcher He Weiwen welcomed Yellen's statement of prosperity and development of China and the United States. "There is a huge difference between China and the United States, so continuous and direct communication is not only constructive, but also vital," he said.

![](Images/cnnytimes/2023-07-10T10-46-21-08-00/09dc-USCHINA-flqt-master1050.jpg)Yellen met with several high -level Chinese leaders involved in economic policies, including China's No. 2 figure and Prime Minister of the State Council. POOL Photo by Mark Schiefelbein

This is especially true during Trump's administration. Before He Lifeng was the vice -prime minister responsible for international economic policy four months ago, Liu He had always held this position. The latter has repeatedly tried to compromise with Steven Manuskin, who has served as the Minister of Finance in the former President Trump's government, reached a compromise on trade and economic issues, but Manuchin could not convince Trump. Trump eventually levied tariffs on extensive Chinese export products for his unfair business behavior.

Many American companies that are connected with China have hoped that the US -China relations will become more friendly after Biden took office, and Chinese officials have such hope. However, US -China relations have not only improved, but also became more tense in the past two years, and in February this year's spy balloon incident, it fell into a complete frozen state.

advertise

Although Yellen's interview is considered a positive step, many experts in China and the United States warn that do not expect the relationship between the two countries to change too much.

"Yellen's trip may allow the tense economic relationship to ease slightly, reminding the United States and China that they have some common business benefits -even if they are weakened -no matter what the situation, they need to make a conversation, maybe they can be on the edge. Improve business exchanges, "Mark Sobel, who had been an official in the US Treasury, said.

However, considering that both countries are worried about national security issues, China has a view that the United States tries to curb its economic development, and the tough political language of the two countries, Sobel said, "It is difficult for Yelun to change the fundamental political dynamics and economic relations. Track. "

![](Images/cnnytimes/2023-07-10T10-46-21-08-00/09dc-USCHINA-zhcg-master1050.jpg)Yellen has lunch with a group of Chinese female economists and entrepreneurs in Beijing, and said that the United States and China can reach consensus in many fields. POOL Photo by Mark Schiefelbein

Although there are differences between China and the United States, Yellen was warmly welcomed in Beijing during the first visit to China as the Minister of Finance.

During the meeting with Premier Li Qiang, the No. 2 Chinese official mentioned that a rainbow appeared in the sky when Yellen arrived at the Capital Airport, saying that this symbolizes the hope of the relationship between the two countries that can be repaired.

On Thursday night, someone saw Yellen a dining in a Yunnan gourmet restaurant. [Chinese official media reported the matter, saying that she could use chopsticks skillfully](https://www.globaltimes.cn/page/202307/1293945.shtml)It is also said that after seeing Yellen's mushroom dishes on social media, the number of people in the restaurant's seats increased significantly.

advertise

Yellen also met with Chinese experts who invested climate and had lunch with a group of Chinese female economists and entrepreneurs. She said that the United States and China can find consensus in many areas.

"Our people have many common things, far more than our differences," Yellen said at lunch.

