# About Yelun Beijing, you should know

Creator: KEITH BRADSHER

Publisher: https://www.facebook.com/nytimeschinese

Published Time: 2023-07-10T11:49:38+08:00

Description: After Yellen held a marathon talks with senior economic officials in China, the severe cold atmosphere between China and the United States eased. When talking about the US's economic strategy to China, she has a gentle wording, but China and the United States continue to adhere to the original position, and they may still face more conflicts in the future. THOMAS Peter/Reuters Minister Jennite Yellen conducted a marathon talk with the new economic policy maker team in Beijing in Beijing.

Images: ["[09USCHINA-TAK...](https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/07/09/multimedia/09USCHINA-TAKEAWAYS-tzjv/09USCHINA-TAKEAWAYS-tzjv-master1050.jpg)"]

Category: 美国

Type: Article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/cnnytimes/2023-07-10T11-49-38-08-00/09USCHINA-TAKEAWAYS-tzjv-master1050.jpg)In the past few days, with the US Treasury Secretary [Jennite Yellen](https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/09/business/janet-yellen-china-us.html)The severe cold atmosphere between China and the United States has eased in a marathon talks in Beijing and a new group of senior economic policy makers.

Yellen is talking about [US economic strategy to China](https://cn.nytimes.com/china/20230707/us-china-relationship-facts/)Time uses a gentle wording, abandoning a saying that it is popular in Washington but offending Beijing. Although Yellen's trip to China may bring more talks, neither she nor Chinese officials shrink back from her own policy position. This makes the two parties face more conflicts in terms of trade, investment and technology in the future.

** She connected with Chinese economic leaders. **

Last fall, [Chinese Communist Party Congress](https://www.nytimes.com/live/2022/10/22/world/china-xi-jinping-congress)For the President of the State [Xi Jinping](https://cn.nytimes.com/china/20221017/china-congress-xi-jinping/)Clear the road and appointed a team loyal to him as a high -level economic position. These officials -including Yellen's peer -to -official official, Vice Premier of the State Council [He Lifeng](https://cn.nytimes.com/china/20230328/xi-jinping-he-lifeng-china-economy/)——In international experience than their predecessors, and Western policy makers are not so familiar with them. China has gradually reduced the release of economic information and stopped many reports, making it more difficult for people to understand the real situation of China's economy.

advertise

One of Yellen's primary goal is to meet the new leadership of China. She also wants to know [China Economy](https://cn.nytimes.com/business/20230629/china-exports-economy/)The current situation, after China has canceled the strict epidemic measures that have been canceled for nearly three years, the rate of rebound in China's economy this year is slower than expected.

Yellen seemed to have achieved some success on these limited goals. She and the four Chinese highest economic policy makers, especially He Lifeng, conducted a total of 10 hours of talks. Although the Biden government has held several rounds of high -level diplomatic talks with China, this is the first time that the government has held such economic talks.

The US Ambassador to China Nicholas Bernes said that re -opening up economic negotiations "is very in line with our interests, and directly conveys tough information on the issues that we have differences. ","

** She used a new word from "D" on the supply chain problem- "Diversity"(diverse)Essence **

Chinese officials are extremely sensitive to diplomatic languages.(decouple)The appeal. They are worried that multinational companies will transfer their extensive supply chains and tens of millions of employment opportunities from China to other countries.

Usla, Chairman of the European Commission, Usula von Delin proposed a gentle and neutral term in March: "[de -risk](https://cn.nytimes.com/world/20230522/decoupling-china-de-risking/) ”(de-risking)Essence Chinese officials and official media initially had no objection to the risk of relief, but one month later, the word of the US national security adviser Jack Shalvin used the word in a speech, and Chinese officials and official media began to condemn the statement.

advertise

During the visit, Yellen tried to dispel China ’s concerns about the United States for decoupling, and even avoid referring to risk. On the contrary, she said that the United States wants a diverse supply chain -this happens to be China's long -term public policy goal.

"One is decoupling, and the other is to diversify or take targeted national security actions for key supply chains. There are important differences between the two," she said.

The Biden government insisted that the recent restrictions on China's high -tech exports -especially for the most advanced semiconductor -just for the US military security. The government tries to describe its actions as a high fence around a small part of the technology.

But even after Yellen's visit, many Chinese people still have skepticism. Wu Xinbo, Dean of the School of International Relations of Shanghai Fudan University, said that if the policy proposed by the United States, "just for national security, the question is that the scope of national security is."

** She did not propose a new policy. There is no China. **

In another statement of the press conference held by Yelun Sunday and another statement of the Chinese official news agency Xinhua News Agency, it is obviously not mentioned whether there are any problems among the many trade, investment and technical issues between the two countries have been resolved.

advertise

In China last Monday to the two key metal 镓 and 锗 used in computer chips [implemented export restrictions](https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/08/business/economy/us-china-chips-janet-yellen.html)Essence The supply of these two materials in the world is almost from China. This export control is widely regarded as revenge on the restrictions on the US semiconductor export of China, although Beijing has not qualitated this measure as revenge. Yelun said in the "Facing the National" program on the Corporation of Columbia Sunday that the move was "possibly" retaliated.

Beijing is also preparing to respond to the investment restrictions on some high -tech fields that the Biden government may make, and this possibility has been discussed for a long time. In 2015, China implemented restrictions on overseas investment. Beijing guides Chinese companies and families not to speculate on American real estate and European football clubs, and promotes them to acquire overseas companies in certain fields, including aircraft production, heavy manufacturing, artificial intelligence, network security and other strategic fields.

Nevertheless, Yellen still tried to show an optimistic attitude towards her visits on Sunday. She tried to refute the unavoidable speculation about conflict.

She said: "The outline of Sino -US relations is not an easy task, but we must never forget that although we face challenges, our path is not destined."

