<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-10T17-38-30-04-00/000000.png) [![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-10T17-38-30-04-00/000001.png)](https://www.rfa.org/mandarin/ytbdzhuantixilie/minying/wy-07102023123033.html/@@images/image)Free Asia Radio Drawing [Audio-Link: https://www.rfa.org/mandarin/ytbdzhuantixilie/minying/wy-07102023123033.html/@stream](https://www.rfa.org/mandarin/ytbdzhuantixilie/minying/wy-07102023123033.html/@@stream)The outside world often summarizes the importance of private enterprises in the Chinese economy with several numbers of "56789". 5 of which refers to private enterprises to contribute 50%of China's taxes, and 9 refers to 90%of the new employment. However, in recent years, the Chinese government has adopted a policy of suppressing and ignoring the private economy, which has greatly hit the confidence of private enterprises. At the end of last year, after China ended the epidemic sealing and entered the channel of economic recovery, the confidence of private enterprises has not been effectively recovered, and it has even dragged down the overall performance of China's economy. This reporter Wang Yuncai wrote three series of reports to reveal the dilemma of China's private economy with the experience of many private entrepreneurs. In the following reports, the current situation of the three services, trading small and micro enterprises will be mainly described.

[** Dancing from the times to Huang Zhong destroy abandonment ｜ The fear and love of Chinese private entrepreneurs (1) **](https://www.rfa.org/mandarin/ytbdzhuantixilie/minying/wy-06142023142320.html)When the Shanghai epidemic was closed in April and May last year, Zhang Kaiyu thought about dying with his two cats.

He has raised these two cats for 10 years, and he said that cats are their own weaknesses. When the news of many people's pets was dispelled by the controlling staff, Zhang Kaiyu was particularly scared. "I can't stand them to death, or I will strangle them by myself. , Just keep them in a cage and open the gas, they will suffocate to death slowly, then I can also use the same way. "

This is the most perfect solution that Zhang Kaiyu can think of, but maybe because there are still sisters and mothers, maybe there is some longing for freedom, and Zhang Kaiyu did not start in the end. But at this time, he had put down his business in his heart.

** Disclosure and defeat ** **

Zhang Kaiyu operated a fashion boutique in Shanghai, and it has been 16 years by 2022. His client is the rich class in Shanghai. On the list of thousands of customers he is in contact, many people have more than tens of millions of net worth. However, after Shanghai was closed in April, these customers gradually disappeared. "Especially in those two months, when talking to friends, they all wanted to leave, and they wanted to leave, including customers and friends, especially customers. Leaving, those who have money are like this. "

Here, you see them, you may have only one, two pieces, or even cheaper, and it is relatively cheap, and it is necessary to think about it, not like buying it like before. "

Zhang Kaiyu quickly figured out a truth, "You see the two months in the past two months, almost everyone seems to be locked in a large prison. There is no freedom. At this time, you feel that the business has no meaning." At the end of the year, Zhang Kaiyu turned his business out.

It was also in 2022, Mr. Mo, in Chengdu (for safety reasons, used a pseudonym) in May in May, and decided to leave the catering industry permanently.

Mr. Mo invested in the catering industry in 2014. It was best to have six restaurants in Chengdu, but by 2022, there were only two fast food restaurants. The fast -food restaurant he finally turned off was still making money, but he finally decided not to do it. "It was unknown at the time. The epidemic in May 2022 was not over. When will it be closed to Chengdu again; in a case, it is two or three months, and you can't do it anymore. Your inventory, your labor, your rent still have to pay. But as soon as the work is stopped, if these money has been invested in, it is completely meaningless. "

![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-10T17-38-30-04-00/000002.png)On September 8, 2020, after the outbreak of the new crown epidemic in Chengdu, a Sichuan opera actor was waiting for customers in a restaurant in Jinli Ancient Street. (Reuters) [![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-10T17-38-30-04-00/000003.png)](https://www.rfa.org/mandarin/ytbdzhuantixilie/minying/wy-07102023123033.html/2020-09-08t102839z_1351177520_rc2aui9fj9fy_rtrmadp_3_health-coronavirus-china.jpg)The consulting company founded by Ge Ping in Hangzhou managed to survive the cool city in 2022, and still chose to "break the business" for its subsidiaries in early 2023. For the sake of safety, "Ge Ping" was interviewed with a pseudonym.

According to the "Regulations on the Registration and Management of Market Estatement", which was implemented in March 2022, the so -called break -out means that if an enterprise encounters a natural disaster, epidemic, etc. Essence However, Ge Ping did not think how many benefits it brought to himself. "Later, it was found that the basic expenditures, financial expenses, taxes of taxes, and renting studios for the expenses of the business are found. For the purpose of protecting the main body, it is not allowed the market to exit too much. The government has this consideration. "

Ge Ping speculated that the government's implementation of this "break" system is to look better on the report, and there are too many companies that do not let the stop or cancel it.

** Love freedom **However, services, trade with Mr. Mo and Mr. Mo encountered difficulties in small and medium -sized enterprises, but not only because of the epidemic and control measures. Before the epidemic began, they had smelled the economy of economy.

Zhang Kaiyu's shop opened in the golden area of the French Concession in Shanghai. The surrounding neighborhoods were large sycamore trees. In his words, it was very "old Shanghai". Before starting a business in 2006, Zhang Kaiyu also worked in the fashion boutique industry. The reason why I opened the store by himself was for freedom. "After opening the store, I basically wake up naturally every day. I go if I love it. I don’t want to go. It's very free. "

With the keen smell and accumulation of the industry, Zhang Kaiyu's store ushered in his peak period ten years later. It is 40%. "But in 2018, Zhang Kaiyu's shop began to go downhill. First, the customer base changed. "20%of the former foreign companies living in Shanghai were foreigners, but 18 years later, these people almost disappeared. At that time, we all felt weird."

At the same time, he found that there were also problems with friends around him. "Several friends were in those two or three years. They actually failed and went bankrupt, and one of them ran out to hide their debts. One of them had done a very good job. Successful, there are nearly a hundred chain stores across the country, and it has failed in those years. "

![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-10T17-38-30-04-00/000004.png)During the epidemic, the Chinese authorities ordered the closure of non -necessary businesses and asked people to work outside a closed fashion shop after working at home. (Associated Press) [![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-10T17-38-30-04-00/000005.png)](https://www.rfa.org/mandarin/ytbdzhuantixilie/minying/wy-07102023123033.html/ap22130261263282.jpg)** Shutan's Day **

Mr. Mo, in Chengdu, also felt that the customer base consumption in his store began in 2018.

Like Zhang Kaiyu, Mr. Mo used to be an office worker. In 2014, due to accidental reasons, Mr. Mo came across the catering industry that he was not familiar with. He opened a buffet restaurant next to the university in Longquanyi, Chengdu, and sold 70 yuan a buffet. Meals, Western food, etc., there are many types, and the price is relatively cheap. It is mainly for young people. You can eat everything. "

This restaurant's positioning is very successful, and it goes smoothly all the way. In the 2016 peak period, the sales of one month can reach 600,000. Mr. Mo quickly opened the second store, the third store ... Mr. Mo said that the day of that time was very comfortable. Basically, every store is profitable. You don't need to make up holes everywhere. At that time, the idea became active.

But in 2018, the business in the store began to decline. Mr. Mo first discovered the change from the consumption of college students. "The store is next to the university. You clearly feel that the pocket money of college students is less. Sometimes I chat with them, they say that the pocket money given by the family is reduced. It is constantly decreasing, so they must reduce their consumption, and you are not just needed when you come out for a meal. "

** Go to the watershed **

But for the reasons for the changes in business in 2018, Zhang Kaiyu and Mr. Mo both felt a little later.

"In 18 years, I didn't feel much, because the business of business is good. The traditional industry has a decline when there is rising, but in 2019, it is not good. I also talk to some colleagues. The feedback is such a situation, "Mr. Mo looked back and found that it was mainly a problem of the economic environment.

"I always feel that there is something wrong, but watching the news network and watching China's official media feel that everything is good," Zhang Kaiyu began to learn research on economics. The answer he found was a problem with the economic structure. "Later, I realized that the real estate tied the economy. The people took most of the money to buy a house, so it caused domestic demand to decline."

In many aspects, 2018 is not like the year of defeat. This year, China's political situation is stable, and Xi Jinping has just started the second term as the leader of the Communist Party of China and the country; five of the new members of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China are newcomers, including Li Zhanshu, Wang Yang and Wang Huning, etc. Do not think that they will have the potential to replace Xi Jinping in the future.

The Chinese economy in 2018 was not particularly worse than other years in the 2010s. The saying about the inflection point of the Chinese economy appeared as early as 2012. In 2018, the Chinese economy still achieved the target of 6.6%of the scheduled GDP (GDP), which seems to be unsatisfactory.

But maybe 2018 is the forty years of reform and opening up in China. People are particularly sensitive to the economic performance of this year. The media pointed out that the growth rate of 6.6%was the lowest economic growth rate in China since 1991. In the separate quarter, the economic growth rate has gradually decreased. , Then 6.7%, 6.5%, and 6.4%.

Economists think that this is the signal of China's economic slowdown, but their explanation of this is so sincere. Some people have the impact of the Sino -US trade war that started this year on China's external economy. Some people think that China's political system is no longer adapted to an increasingly complex economic pattern. In the early 1990s, he predicted that the rise of the rise of China's Economic Harvard University, Dr. Williamoverholt, published a new book "China's Crisis OFSUCCESS" in 2018, and believes that the Chinese economy has gone to the watershed corridor. It can maintain success unless it is transformed into a more market -oriented economy.

![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-10T17-38-30-04-00/000006.png)The cover of the book "China's Crisis of Success" published in 2018. Book author Williamoverholt, a professor at Harvard University in the United States, believes that the Chinese economy has reached a watershed and unless it is transformed into a more market -oriented economy to maintain success. (Screenshot of Amazon's official website) [![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-10T17-38-30-04-00/000007.png)](https://www.rfa.org/mandarin/ytbdzhuantixilie/minying/wy-07102023123033.html/wy3.jpg)** Avoid it or not be too late **Zhang Kaiyu retired half of the store in 2018. "One month calculates various costs, including rent, employees, and the cost of pressing goods and the cost of management. It is estimated that it can save 30,000 to 40,000 a month."

Mr. Mo began to close the shop, "it was closed one after another, because there were more than one, from 2019, until 2022, the final closing was May 2022."

Although the economic situation is not good, the two bosses feel that their business environment has passed. Although the government authorities are disturbing their operations from time to time, they generally feel that regardless of Shanghai or Chengdu, they can be regarded as friendly cities in China.

Mr. Mo said that he had been a restaurant for a few years. Although he also encountered difficulties from the government authority, he could basically avoid it. Just go flexibly and don't be sticking to them. Generally, I think it's okay, and it's not too embarrassed. "

He said "not too embarrassed" several times: once, the restaurant was issued by 600,000 penalties because the fire protection facilities had not passed, but they were actually not fined; In this case, I just scare you and scare you. I do n’t want you, I may find some trouble, but in fact, I do n’t. ”

But at the same time, Mr. Mo has also received benefits from the Chengdu government's policy. Mr. Mo's buffet restaurant has won an award at the Chengdu Food Festival in 2018, and has been preferentially treated in loans, and has received a loan of the expansion brand.

At the same time, Zhang Kaiyu, who is in Shanghai, will worry about unnecessary administrative intervention in the store from time to time. "His intervention will be a lot, such as asking your signboards to be unified, and the design of the store should be done according to his aesthetics, but you Knowing that their aesthetics are bad, it is a very beautiful store, which will be very ugly by them. "

Chen Kaiyu said sighingly that his bottom line was relatively low. "The Chinese have basically come back to the habit. For this kind of thing, we all think that as long as it does not care about you, we are grateful."

Zhang Kaiyu and Mr. Mo were afraid of avoiding the government, and Ge Ping of Hangzhou began in 2018. His business has close ties with the government.

** All the heads are head companies **

Ge Ping started a work in the enterprise before starting a business and conducted management consulting. After starting the business, it also mainly took the contract business from the enterprise and the government in this field. The business he did for the government also includes consultation with a stability maintenance mechanism, that is, to prevent the government's response mechanism consultation from social vicious incidents.

Ge Ping knows the doorway of the government business, "Especially for government consultation, in fact, it is still power to find rent. The reason why this business is for you may be because you know a certain official. He has your professionalism. Objective evaluation, and then you can also give him some benefits and exchanging benefits in private. "He emphasized that there are also bidding on the surface of this business government, but all such bidding is internal.

With the accurate grasp of the network and the wind direction of the industry, Ge Ping's company quickly reached a height of the industry in 2019. "The best time, about 400,000 contracts signed a year, which refers to pure income. We are the income. It belongs to a small and micro enterprise, and it can reach the top ten in this area. "

But whether it is Ge Ping, a consulting company that has a certain binding with the government's interests, or Mr. Mo's catering company, or Zhang Kaiyu's fashion boutique, in normal times, he must handle the relationship with the government trembling. Under the government's one -size -fits -all sealing policy, it is difficult to get necessary help from the government.

Ge Ping's biggest complaint is that his enterprise was too small to rescue from the Hangzhou government during the epidemic. "The only policy I got by my company was after the outbreak of (the epidemic), there were ten consecutive months. Fees reduced the operating cost of the enterprise. "

During the epidemic, Ge Ping's consulting company's contract was reduced; because of the lack of money in the local government, some of the company's government contracts could not be renewed. Due to the consultation, Ge Ping understands the mentality of different enterprises in the market. "For small and micro enterprises like us, from the perspective of the market, where does this confidence come from? From the perspective of most enterprises, the epidemic situation In three years, (government aspect) has not had any communication with our business owners. "

The government's assistance seems to be far away from the Ge Ping, but it is closer to some other companies. It can be seen in the "A solid and stable Economic Policy" released by the State Council of China in early June 2022 that it can be seen that in terms of financing, re -production and re -production policies, the central government supports key enterprises.

The "Measures" also mentioned that it has handled the tax refund of small and micro enterprises and individual industrial and commercial households and increased its assistance. According to the China Official Media People's Daily Report earlier this year, in 2022, small and micro enterprises and individual industrial and commercial households increased tax cuts, fees, and tax refunds and slowing fees exceeding 1.7 trillion yuan, accounting become. But these policies have not felt the actual discounts in the three policies.

Ge Ping keenly noticed the logic behind these policies. "My personal perception is that the government has not installed it in the past two years. The company is a listed company in A -share, and the government comes based on this level. "

** Bone injury to bones **

In fact, different local governments have some preferential policies for SMEs. Mr. Mo's Chengdu has a policy of stabilizing enterprises before the epidemic. Each employee of Mr. Mo's restaurant has received a subsidy of about 100 yuan a month. This policy continued during the three years of the epidemic.

However, these cultivation and supplementary policies seem to be difficult to save the predicament of the epidemic seal that makes it unable to operate normally.

Mr. Mo remembered the three years of the epidemic, and it was no longer the meaning of Shu Tan during the peak of 2016. "I stayed at home for two months. It is estimated that this level must be a bit sad. Then I also gave the family back to the family. I said that I did n’t know what the situation was.

Even with such determination, Mr. Mo still feels stressed all the time. "Because you have to pay wages every day, there are so many employees, they still have to eat, right?" And even if Mr. Mo's rent is in the epidemic situation During this period, it is still increasing at a rate of 6%per year.

Mr. Mo is currently in California, USA. He has a clear contrast to the epidemic measures of both China and the United States. "It's been too long. I thought it was almost let go of the three months at that time, but I really did not expect these three. After the year, people are hurting their bones. Anyway, many people in my circle fall in this place, that is, a fatal blow. This blow is knocking on the brain!"

** Society in the eyes of the owner **

Under the control of the scary epidemic, Mr. Mo saw not only the downside of the businessmen around him, but also the fission of the entire social atmosphere. "The riders were uncle aunts and the like before, and later they were very young. The beautiful little girl came to takeaway, and when I talked, many of them were from the beginning of the high education to send takeaway, which means that the entire employment status is not very good. "

From the takeaway rider, Mr. Mo directly realized the true emotions of Chinese society. "I feel that they have suffered a lot of social pressure. If you come quickly, you can urge it. I often quarrel with my employees and conflict. "Mr. Mo had to always appease his employees so that they must hold back and do not work with the takeaway.Mr. Mo said that the situation he saw was particularly serious in 2021-2022. Actually, after the outbreak of the new crown epidemic in early 2020, as the economy fluctuated, the employment situation of Chinese society experienced ups and downs. In 2021, many places resumed work and re -production, and the unemployment rate fell, but from the second half of that year, China's unemployment rate has risen again. As far as the data released by the National Bureau of Statistics of China, in April 2022, on the eve of Mr. Mo's closure of the last restaurant, the national urban survey rate was 6.1%, especially the youth group (16-24 years old) surveying an unemployment rate was as high as 18.2% (In April 2023, this number has risen to 20.4%).

Facing the forced economic space and the worsening social situation, there seems to be more ways to go. Zhang Kaiyu observed from the rich class that he was in contact with himself, "The most dynamic and richest people in the whole society, what I said is those who have done very successfully through legitimate operation. These people are actually engines of the entire economy. People are the most capable of leaving, and they are the most consciously left. I think these people are leaving, or they have left. "

But in his opinion, this is only the choice of very few people. "For most ordinary shopkeepers, or small and medium entrepreneurs, they can't leave, they can only struggle here and struggle to survive."

Zhang Kaiyu and his cat moved to California, USA in March 2023. Although China had ended the clearing policy at that time, he was still full of disappointment. "He has not learned this policy because he has learned from the world what lessons have learned from the world from the world. "He seemed to be glad to say this secret, laughed twice, and said," He just can't persist because he can't hold on, or the common people resist too much; Pay attention to the health of the people, or the right to survive the basic rights, etc. "."

The society that Ge Ping saw in Hangzhou was the resistance of the people. On the evening of November 27, 2022, the white paper movement was spreading the most widely in the country. Ge Ping ran to the scene of the Hangzhou White Paper Movement, near the Apple computer store near the West Lake, "to the back, those young people, including those, including Some girls are completely a "Chongta" posture. Before eight o'clock, all the siege circles of their (police) had been arranged, including their leadership at this time, and there was a car. I could see it. It is clear, but there are still some young people to rush the tower. "

In this social movement that has not been seen in China for many years, Ge Ping saw the hope of society. At the same time, he had a new discovery from the perspective of maintaining the stability system: local governments were lying flat when dealing with this incident, "Why white paper The revolution occurred in dozens of cities. In fact, in this and in the stability maintenance mechanism, they had slacks at that time, and we could see that we can see the online security data in the background. "He believes that this also reflects the progress of a certain society.

![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-10T17-38-30-04-00/000010.png)On November 27, 2022, the protesters raised white paper on the streets of Beijing to oppose the Chinese government's epidemic prevention policy. (Federation of the Associated Press)

** "Investigate 11 years" ** **

After the White Paper Sports swept the country, the Chinese government quickly ended the epidemic sealing policy at the end of last year, and it has been more than half a year to this day. Chinese society seems to be slowly moving towards the right track, healing the harm caused by the three years of sealing the epidemic.

Three small business owners from Chengdu, Shanghai and Hangzhou have made arrangements for their destiny. Mr. Mo said that when he ran to the United States, he came to hide his debt. He was reluctant to talk about the future of the catering industry. "To be honest, when I can recover, I don't want to care about this. Secondly, I am not in the country, and care about care. "

Zhang Kaiyu was a little worried. His mother was in a domestic stroke not long ago. He could not speak in the intensive care unit, but his sister warned him not to go back. Ge Ping said that he would take a step in a step, and he is currently not available for the time being; his company still has six employees. Although he loses money, he also pays them.

The confidence of domestic private enterprises has not recovered. The Chinese government also seems to understand the situation of private enterprises. In recent months, local governments have successively held seminars with private entrepreneurs. In early July, Zheng Zujie, director of the National Development and Reform Commission of China, negotiated with the heads of five private enterprises such as Sanyi Group and Nongfu Spring.

But what the small owners are actually watching in private enterprises. "Anyone who is a bit rational knows that this environment has reached a very bad level," Zhang Kaiyu sighed.

At the end of 2020, Ant Financial's listing plan was stopped at the last moment, which is generally considered to be a sign of the Chinese government's round of suppression of private enterprises. On July 7 this year, the Chinese financial regulatory authorities announced that the Ant Group's fines and confiscated illegal income were 7.1 billion yuan.

In the second quarter of this year, the Xiamen Taxation Bureau of the State Administration of Taxation pursued the tax evasion of local Taoxiang Catering Co., Ltd. from 2012 to 2015. Netizens spread the news on the Internet with the title of "11 years of inspection", which is full of warning.

These practices seem to have legal and policies, but Zhang Kaiyu said that he could not see the border with various governments. "The key is that he can use his power arbitrarily, want you to give birth, and let you die if you want you to die. Dead, there is no legal boundary. "

Ge Ping, who often deal with the government, believes that for small and medium -oriented private enterprises, it is difficult to change the business environment. "It is now a government platform for the head of the header, but after the platform, can these heads survive? For example Real estate companies, can their problems be resolved? If the head enterprises are not good, then you expect that small and medium -sized enterprises will become better. There is no scientific basis for this. "

Ge Ping also provided entrepreneurial counseling for college students in college, but he held a negative attitude towards the current entrepreneurial environment. "The current market environment, I want to give a suggestion, that is, the risk is too high, the policy support is too small, just like the epidemic situation, just like the epidemic situation. During this time, what support do you have to entrepreneurs? Without any support, it is to let them die. "

** Our living method and our expectations **

However, after experiencing the white paper movement, Ge Ping has a different kind of optimism about the power of Chinese society itself. "At present, the people's wisdom has been opened, just to know more about history, especially to know the country of the Communist Party of China How does the machine operate. "

He hinted that for each individual, to recognize his class and expectations for life, "the second or rich two generations have their living law, but we ordinary people, whether it is technology, Still work or be a businessman, we have to have our living law, we have to have our expectations!"

